(29, 'eretmochelys', 'imbricata', '', 'hawksbill sea turtle', '', '', '', 'testudines', 'turtles', 'hawksbill sea turtles', '', 'testudines', 'fitzinger', 'linnaeus', '{&quot;1843&quot;:&quot;1766&quot;}', '', 'Although many recent authors have abandoned use of Atlantic versus Indo-Pacific Ocean subspecies (Meylan, 2006, Chelon. Res. Monogr. 3: 105&ndash;127), the names have not been formally synonymized.  Because mitochondrial genome comparisons by Okayama et al. (1999, Chelon. Conserv. Biol. 3: 362&ndash;367) suggested genetic divergence between the Caribbean and Indo-Pacific populations, we retain the subspecies names pending further study.', 'michelle koo', 'John B. Iverson (Chair), Peter A. Meylan, Michael E. Seidel', '', 0, 0, 0),
(30, 'eretmochelys', 'imbricata', 'bissa', 'pacific hawksbill sea turtle', '', '', '', 'testudines', 'turtles', 'hawksbill sea turtles', '', 'testudines', 'fitzinger', 'r', '{&quot;1843&quot;:&quot;1835&quot;}', '', 'Although many recent authors have abandoned use of Atlantic versus Indo-Pacific Ocean subspecies (Meylan, 2006, Chelon. Res. Monogr. 3: 105&ndash;127), the names have not been formally synonymized.  Because mitochondrial genome comparisons by Okayama et al. (1999, Chelon. Conserv. Biol. 3: 362&ndash;367) suggested genetic divergence between the Caribbean and Indo-Pacific populations, we retain the subspecies names pending further study.', 'michelle koo', 'John B. Iverson (Chair), Peter A. Meylan, Michael E. Seidel', '', 0, 0, 0),
(31, 'eretmochelys', 'imbricata', 'imbricata', 'atlantic hawksbill sea turtle', '', '', '', 'testudines', 'turtles', 'hawksbill sea turtles', '', 'testudines', 'fitzinger', 'linnaeus', '{&quot;1843&quot;:&quot;1766&quot;}', '', 'Although many recent authors have abandoned use of Atlantic versus Indo-Pacific Ocean subspecies (Meylan, 2006, Chelon. Res. Monogr. 3: 105&ndash;127), the names have not been formally synonymized.  Because mitochondrial genome comparisons by Okayama et al. (1999, Chelon. Conserv. Biol. 3: 362&ndash;367) suggested genetic divergence between the Caribbean and Indo-Pacific populations, we retain the subspecies names pending further study.', 'michelle koo', 'John B. Iverson (Chair), Peter A. Meylan, Michael E. Seidel', '', 0, 0, 0),
