(34, 'gopherus', 'agassizii', '', 'mohave desert tortoise', 'species&#95;photos/Gopherus&#95;agassizii.jpg', 'Philip Kahn', 'CC BY-SA 3.0', 'testudines', 'turtles', 'gopher tortoises', '', 'testudines', 'rafinesque', 'cooper', '{&quot;1832&quot;:&quot;1861&quot;}', '', 'See note under *G. morafkai*. The spelling of the standard English name has been changed from &ldquo;Mojave&rdquo; to &ldquo;Mohave&rdquo; for consistency with other names in the list (see note for *Crotalus scutulatus*).', 'philip kahn', 'John B. Iverson (Chair), Peter A. Meylan, Michael E. Seidel', '', 0, 0, 0),
(35, 'gopherus', 'berlandieri', '', 'berlandier&amp;#39;s tortoise', '', '', '', 'testudines', 'turtles', 'gopher tortoises', '', 'testudines', 'rafinesque', 'agassiz', '{&quot;1832&quot;:&quot;1857&quot;}', '', 'Because most of the range of this tortoise is in Mexico (not Texas), we follow Ernst and Lovich (2009, Turtles of the United States and Canada. Second Edition.  Johns Hopkins Univ. Press, Baltimore) in using the patronym Berlandier&#39;s Tortoise, rather than the frequently used name of Texas Tortoise.', 'michelle koo', 'John B. Iverson (Chair), Peter A. Meylan, Michael E. Seidel', '', 0, 0, 0),
(36, 'gopherus', 'morafkai', '', 'sonoran desert tortoise', '', '', '', 'testudines', 'turtles', 'gopher tortoises', '', 'testudines', 'rafinesque', 'murphy, berry, edwards, leviton, lathrop, and riedle', '{&quot;1832&quot;:&quot;2011&quot;}', '', 'This cryptic species was formerly included in *G. agassizii* (Murphy et al., 2011, ZooKeys 113: 39&ndash;71).  The original description noted that *G. morafkai* occurs in the Sonoran desert as well as part of the Mohave Desert and part of the Sinaloan thornscrub, and that the restricted *G. agassizii* occurs in the Mohave Desert as well as part of the Sonoran Desert.  Hence, the authors recommended the patronyms Morafka&rsquo;s Desert Tortoise and Agassiz&rsquo;s Desert Tortoise, respectively, rather than the geographic names Sonoran Desert Tortoise (often abbreviated SDT) and Mohave Desert Tortoise (MDT), reflecting their primary distributions.  However, because the latter names have long been used as standard names for these two populations (including legislation by the US Fish and Wildlife Service), and because of the potential for confusion of the abbreviation for Morafka&rsquo;s Desert Tortoise (also MDT) with that for the Mohave Desert Tortoise, we support the use of the traditional geographic standard names.', 'michelle koo', 'John B. Iverson (Chair), Peter A. Meylan, Michael E. Seidel', '', 0, 0, 0),
(37, 'gopherus', 'polyphaemus', '', 'gopher tortoise', '', '', '', 'testudines', 'turtles', 'gopher tortoises', '', 'testudines', 'rafinesque', 'daudin', '{"1832": "1802"}', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0, 0),
(38, 'graptemys', 'barbouri', '', 'barbour&amp;#39;s map turtle', '', '', '', 'testudines', 'turtles', 'map turtles', '', 'testudines', 'agassiz', 'carr and marchand', '{&quot;1857&quot;:&quot;1942&quot;}', '', 'Note on genus:  \nEvidence for monophyly and content of this genus was reviewed by Dobie (1981, Tulane Stud. Zool. Bot. 23: 85), Lamb and Osentoski (1997, J. Herpetol. 31: 258&ndash;265), and Stephens and Wiens (2003, Biol. J. Linn. Soc. 79: 577&ndash;610).', 'michelle koo', 'John B. Iverson (Chair), Peter A. Meylan, Michael E. Seidel', '', 0, 0, 0),
(39, 'graptemys', 'caglei', '', 'cagle&amp;#39;s map turtle', '', '', '', 'testudines', 'turtles', 'map turtles', '', 'testudines', 'agassiz', 'haynes and mckown', '{&quot;1857&quot;:&quot;1974&quot;}', '', 'Note on genus:  \nEvidence for monophyly and content of this genus was reviewed by Dobie (1981, Tulane Stud. Zool. Bot. 23: 85), Lamb and Osentoski (1997, J. Herpetol. 31: 258&ndash;265), and Stephens and Wiens (2003, Biol. J. Linn. Soc. 79: 577&ndash;610).', 'michelle koo', 'John B. Iverson (Chair), Peter A. Meylan, Michael E. Seidel', '', 0, 0, 0),
(40, 'graptemys', 'ernsti', '', 'escambia map turtle', '', '', '', 'testudines', 'turtles', 'map turtles', '', 'testudines', 'agassiz', 'lovich and mccoy', '{&quot;1857&quot;:&quot;1992&quot;}', '', 'Note on genus:  \nEvidence for monophyly and content of this genus was reviewed by Dobie (1981, Tulane Stud. Zool. Bot. 23: 85), Lamb and Osentoski (1997, J. Herpetol. 31: 258&ndash;265), and Stephens and Wiens (2003, Biol. J. Linn. Soc. 79: 577&ndash;610).', 'michelle koo', 'John B. Iverson (Chair), Peter A. Meylan, Michael E. Seidel', '', 0, 0, 0),
(41, 'graptemys', 'flavimaculata', '', 'yellow-blotched map turtle', '', '', '', 'testudines', 'turtles', 'map turtles', '', 'testudines', 'agassiz', 'cagle', '{&quot;1857&quot;:&quot;1954&quot;}', '', 'Ennen et al. (2010, J. Herpetol. 44: 544-554) argued for the continued recognition of this species and the closely related *G. oculifera*, despite their limited genetic divergence.  \n\nNote on genus:  \nEvidence for monophyly and content of this genus was reviewed by Dobie (1981, Tulane Stud. Zool. Bot. 23: 85), Lamb and Osentoski (1997, J. Herpetol. 31: 258&ndash;265), and Stephens and Wiens (2003, Biol. J. Linn. Soc. 79: 577&ndash;610).', 'michelle koo', 'John B. Iverson (Chair), Peter A. Meylan, Michael E. Seidel', '', 0, 0, 0),
(42, 'graptemys', 'geographica', '', 'northern map turtle', '', '', '', 'testudines', 'turtles', 'map turtles', '', 'testudines', 'agassiz', 'lesueur', '{&quot;1857&quot;:&quot;1817&quot;}', '', 'We do not refer to this species as the Common Map Turtle because of the possibility that the word &amp;#39;common&amp;#39; might be misinterpreted to imply abundance rather than to the fact that it has a broad geographic distribution.\n\nNote on genus:  \nEvidence for monophyly and content of this genus was reviewed by Dobie (1981, Tulane Stud. Zool. Bot. 23: 85), Lamb and Osentoski (1997, J. Herpetol. 31: 258&ndash;265), and Stephens and Wiens (2003, Biol. J. Linn. Soc. 79: 577&ndash;610).', 'michelle koo', 'John B. Iverson (Chair), Peter A. Meylan, Michael E. Seidel', '', 0, 0, 0),
