(54, 'graptemys', 'sabinensis', '', 'sabine map turtle', '', '', '', 'testudines', 'turtles', 'map turtles', '', 'testudines', 'agassiz', 'cagle', '{&quot;1857&quot;:&quot;1953&quot;}', '', 'Although *sabinensis* has been considered a subspecies of *G. ouachitensis* by most authors since Vogt (1980, Tulane Stud. Zool. Bot. 22: 17&ndash;48), the morphological and molecular evidence for its species status has slowly been mounting (Ward, 1980, Ph.D. dissertation, North Carolina State Univ.; Stephens and Wiens, 2003, Biol. J. Linn. Soc. 79: 577&ndash;610; Myers, 2008, Ph.D. dissertation, Iowa State Univ.; Wiens et al., 2010, Biol. J. Linn. Soc. 99: 445&ndash;461; Brown et al., 2012, Copeia 2012: 301&ndash;306).  Based on these data and his own field sampling, Lindeman (2013, Univ. Oklahoma Press, Norman) noted that *sabinensis* is allopatric, non-intergrading, and diagnosable, and formally elevated it to a full species.  \n\nNote on genus:  \nEvidence for monophyly and content of this genus was reviewed by Dobie (1981, Tulane Stud. Zool. Bot. 23: 85), Lamb and Osentoski (1997, J. Herpetol. 31: 258&ndash;265), and Stephens and Wiens (2003, Biol. J. Linn. Soc. 79: 577&ndash;610).', 'michelle koo', 'John B. Iverson (Chair), Peter A. Meylan, Michael E. Seidel', '', 0, 0, 0),
