(56, 'kinosternon', 'arizonense', '', 'arizona mud turtle', '', '', '', 'testudines', 'turtles', 'american mud turtles', '', 'testudines', 'spix', 'gilmore', '{&quot;1824&quot;:&quot;1922&quot;}', '', 'Formerly a subspecies of *K. flavescens*, Serb et al. (2001, Mol. Phylogenet. Evol. 18: 149&ndash;162) demonstrated that including this taxon in *K. flavescens* made the latter paraphyletic with respect to *K. baurii* and *K. subrubrum*.  They recommended recognition as a species.  In addition, Iverson (1989, Southwest. Natur. 34: 356&ndash;368) demonstrated the distinctiveness of this form, confirmed its allopatry with *K. flavescens*, and suggested that its reproductive season is asynchronous with that of *K. flavescens*.', 'michelle koo', 'John B. Iverson (Chair), Peter A. Meylan, Michael E. Seidel', '', 0, 0, 0),
(57, 'kinosternon', 'baurii', '', 'striped mud turtle', '', '', '', 'testudines', 'turtles', 'american mud turtles', '', 'testudines', 'spix', 'garman', '{"1824": "1891"}', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0, 0),
(58, 'kinosternon', 'flavescens', '', 'yellow mud turtle', '', '', '', 'testudines', 'turtles', 'american mud turtles', '', 'testudines', 'spix', 'agassiz', '{&quot;1824&quot;:&quot;1857&quot;}', '', 'The validity of the subspecies *Kinosternon flavescens spooneri* Smith, 1951 (Illinois Mud Turtle) has been questioned on morphological and molecular grounds by Houseal et al. (1982, Copeia 1982: 567&ndash;580), Berry and Berry (1984, Ann. Carnegie Mus. Nat. Hist. 53: 185&ndash;206), and Serb et al. (2001, Mol. Phylogenet. Evol. 18: 149&ndash;162).', 'michelle koo', 'John B. Iverson (Chair), Peter A. Meylan, Michael E. Seidel', '', 0, 0, 0),
(59, 'kinosternon', 'hirtipes', '', 'rough-footed mud turtle', '', '', '', 'testudines', 'turtles', 'american mud turtles', '', 'testudines', 'spix', 'wagler', '{&quot;1824&quot;:&quot;1830&quot;}', '', 'Collins (1997, SSAR Herpetol. Circ. 25) suggested the name Mexican Mud Turtle for this turtle, but that name is generally applied to *Kinosternon integrum* (Iverson et al., 1998, Cat. Am. Amph. Rept. 652).', 'michelle koo', 'John B. Iverson (Chair), Peter A. Meylan, Michael E. Seidel', '', 0, 0, 0),
