(87, 'pseudemys', 'peninsularis', '', 'peninsular cooter', '', '', '', 'testudines', 'turtles', 'cooters', '', 'testudines', 'gray', 'carr', '{&quot;1856&quot;:&quot;1938&quot;}', '', 'Formerly considered a subspecies of *P. floridana* (Conant and Collins, 1992, A Field Guide to Reptiles and Amphibians: Eastern and Central North America. Houghton Mifflin Co., Boston), Seidel (1994, Chelon. Conserv. Biol. 1: 117&ndash;130) elevated this form to a species.  He demonstrated that *peninsularis* does not intergrade with *P. c. floridana* in northern Florida, that it is sympatric with *P. suwanniensis*, and that there are morphometric and osteological characters (as well as markings) which consistently distinguish it from *P. concinna*.  However, Thomas and Jansen (2006, Chelon. Res. Monogr. 3: 338&ndash;347) recommended the recognition of this form as a subspecies of *P. floridana*.', 'michelle koo', 'John B. Iverson (Chair), Peter A. Meylan, Michael E. Seidel', '', 0, 0, 0),
(88, 'pseudemys', 'rubriventris', '', 'northern red-bellied cooter', '', '', '', 'testudines', 'turtles', 'cooters', '', 'testudines', 'gray', 'leconte', '{"1856": "1830"}', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0, 0),
(89, 'pseudemys', 'suwanniensis', '', 'suwannee cooter', '', '', '', 'testudines', 'turtles', 'cooters', '', 'testudines', 'gray', 'carr', '{&quot;1856&quot;:&quot;1937&quot;}', '', 'Seidel (1994, Chelon. Conserv. Biol. 1: 117&ndash;130) elevated this form from a subspecies of *P. concinna* to a species based on his belief that it is allopatric or parapatric with other members of the *concinna* group.  However, Jackson (1995, Chelon. Conserv. Biol. 1: 329&ndash;333) believed that it may intergrade with *P. c. concinna* in northern Florida and thus does not deserve species status.  Recent availability of material from the Gulf Hammock region of northwest Florida is reviewed by Jackson (2006, Chelon. Res Monogr. 3: 325&ndash;337), who recommended recognition of this form as a subspecies of *P. concinna*.', 'michelle koo', 'John B. Iverson (Chair), Peter A. Meylan, Michael E. Seidel', '', 0, 0, 0),
