(139, 'charina', 'bottae', '', 'northern rubber boa', '', '', '', 'squamata', 'snakes', 'rubber boas', '', 'serpentes', 'gray', 'blainville', '{&quot;1849&quot;:&quot;1835&quot;}', '', 'Kluge (1993, Zool. J. Linn. Soc. 107: 293&ndash;351) placed *Lichanura* in the synonymy of *Charina* because they formed sister taxa. Burbrink (2005, Mol. Phylogenet. Evo. 34: 167&ndash;180) corroborated the relationship found by Kluge. Rodr&iacute;guez-Robles et al. (2001, Mol. Phylogenet. Evol. 18: 227&ndash;237) found *C. b. umbratica* to be morphologically and geographically distinct and were elevated to species status based in part on lineages using mtDNA evidence along with with allozyme data from a previous study (Weisman, 1988, MS Thesis, CSU Polytechnic Pomona). With the recognition of *C. umbratica* and fossil species referred to both *Charina* and *Lichanura* (Holman, 2000, Fossil Snakes of North America, Indiana Univ. Press), neither genus is monotypic, and they are treated here as separate genera.', 'carol spencer', 'Brian I. Crother (Chair), Jeff Boundy, Frank T. Burbrink, Jonathan A. Campbell, R. Alexander Pyron', '2014-12-12', 1, 1, 0),
(140, 'charina', 'umbratica', '', 'southern rubber boa', '', '', '', 'squamata', 'snakes', 'rubber boas', '', 'serpentes', 'gray', 'klauber', '{&quot;1849&quot;:&quot;1943&quot;}', '', 'Kluge (1993, Zool. J. Linn. Soc. 107: 293&ndash;351) placed *Lichanura* in the synonymy of *Charina* because they formed sister taxa. Burbrink (2005, Mol. Phylogenet. Evo. 34: 167&ndash;180) corroborated the relationship found by Kluge. Rodr&iacute;guez-Robles et al. (2001, Mol. Phylogenet. Evol. 18: 227&ndash;237) found *C. b. umbratica* to be morphologically and geographically distinct and were elevated to species status based in part on lineages using mtDNA evidence along with with allozyme data from a previous study (Weisman, 1988, MS Thesis, CSU Polytechnic Pomona). With the recognition of *C. umbratica* and fossil species referred to both *Charina* and *Lichanura* (Holman, 2000, Fossil Snakes of North America, Indiana Univ. Press), neither genus is monotypic, and they are treated here as separate genera.', 'carol spencer', 'Brian I. Crother (Chair), Jeff Boundy, Frank T. Burbrink, Jonathan A. Campbell, R. Alexander Pyron', '2014-12-12', 1, 0, 0),
(141, 'chilomeniscus', 'stramineus', '', 'variable sandsnake', '', '', '', 'squamata', 'snakes', 'sandsnakes', '', 'serpentes', 'cope', 'cope', '{&quot;1860&quot;:&quot;1860&quot;}', '', 'Grismer et al. (2002, Herpetologica 58: 18&ndash;31) found the previously recognized species *C. cinctus, C. punctatissimus*, and *C. stramineus* to represent morphotypes of a single species.', 'carol spencer', 'Brian I. Crother (Chair), Jeff Boundy, Frank T. Burbrink, Jonathan A. Campbell, R. Alexander Pyron', '2014-12-12', 0, 0, 0),
(142, 'chionactis', 'occipitalis', '', 'western shovel-nosed snake', '', '', '', 'squamata', 'snakes', 'shovel-nosed snakes', '', 'serpentes', 'cope', 'hallowell', '{&quot;1860&quot;:&quot;1854&quot;}', '', '', 'carol spencer', 'Brian I. Crother (Chair), Jeff Boundy, Frank T. Burbrink, Jonathan A. Campbell, R. Alexander Pyron', '2014-12-12', 0, 1, 0),
(143, 'chionactis', 'occipitalis', 'annulata', 'colorado desert shovel-nosed snake', '', '', '', 'squamata', 'snakes', 'shovel-nosed snakes', '', 'serpentes', 'cope', 'baird', '{&quot;1860&quot;:&quot;1859&quot;}', '', 'There is some question as to the validity of the name *C. saxatilis* (Funk, 1967, Southwest Nat. 12: 180), the Gila Mountains Shovel-nosed Snake, which is generally considered to be a synonym of *C. o. annulata* (see Cross, 1978, Ph.D. dissertation, Univ. Arizona). Mahrdt et al. (2001, Cat. Am. Amph. Rept. 730) considered *C. saxatilis* a synonym of *C. o. annulata*. Wood et al. (2008, Cons. Gen. 9: 1489&ndash;1507) demonstrated, using mtDNA and morphological data, that population structure was not concordant with the traditional subspecific taxonomy. They also revealed two potentially, independent evolutionary lineages. Year for Baird is possibly 1858.', 'carol spencer', 'Brian I. Crother (Chair), Jeff Boundy, Frank T. Burbrink, Jonathan A. Campbell, R. Alexander Pyron', '2014-12-12', 0, 1, 0),
