(455, 'ambystoma', 'jeffersonianum', '', 'jefferson salamander', '', '', '', 'caudata', 'salamanders', 'mole salamanders', '', 'caudata', 'tschudi', 'green', '{&quot;1838&quot;:&quot;1827&quot;}', '', 'Taxonomic recognition of asexual forms that combine genomes of this species, *A. laterale*, *A. texanum*, and *A. tigrinum* raises complex issues.  These include discordance between cytoplasmic and nuclear genes, reticulate evolution, and genome - swapping (Bogart, 2003, in Sever, D.M. [ed.], Reproductive Biology and Phylogeny of Urodela, Science Publishers, Inc., Pp. 109-134). Bi and Bogart (2010, BMC Evol. Biol. 10: 238) confirm an ancient origin for the mitochondrial genome shared by asexual forms of this complex. Dubois and Rafa&euml;lli (2012, Alytes 28: 77&ndash;161) resurrected the name *platineum* for the asexual forms.   ', 'michelle koo', 'Stephen G. Tilley (Chair), Richard Highton, David B. Wake', '', 0, 0, 0),
