(497, 'batrachoseps', 'major', '', 'southern california slender salamander', '', '', '', 'caudata', 'salamanders', 'slender salamanders', '', 'caudata', 'bonaparte', 'camp', '{&quot;1839&quot;:&quot;1915&quot;}', '', 'Fouquette and Dubois (2014, A Checklist of North American Amphibians and Reptiles, The United States and Canada, Seventh Edition, Vol. 1 &ndash; Amphibians, Xlibris, San Bernardino, CA, 613 p.) follow Hansen and Wake (2005, in Lannoo M., [ed.], Amphibian Declines, Status of United States Species, Univ. California Press, Pp. 666&ndash;667) in treating this form as a full species. The status of this taxon is considered in Mart&iacute;nez-Solano et al. (2012, Mol. Phylog. Evol. 63: 131&ndash;149), who document discordance between nuclear and mitochondrial sequence data in *B. major*. *B. m. aridus* is one of six clades of &ldquo;southern&rdquo; major with mtDNA data, but &ldquo;northern&rdquo; and &ldquo;southern&rdquo; components of major are not supported by data from nuclear genes.', 'michelle koo', 'Stephen G. Tilley (Chair), Richard Highton, David B. Wake', '', 0, 0, 0);
