(514, 'desmognathus', 'apalachicolae', '', 'apalachiola dusky salamander', '', '', '', 'caudata', 'salamanders', 'dusky salamanders', '', 'caudata', 'baird', 'means and karlin', '{"1850": "1989"}', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0, 0),
(515, 'desmognathus', 'auriculatus', '', 'southern dusky salamander', '', '', '', 'caudata', 'salamanders', 'dusky salamanders', '', 'caudata', 'baird', 'holbrook', '{&quot;1850&quot;:&quot;1838&quot;}', '', 'Divergent mitochondrial DNA lineages occur among Atlantic Coastal Plain populations that are morphologically assignable to this species. These lineages do not comprise a monophyletic unit (Beamer and Lamb, 2008, Mol. Phylogenet. Evol. 47: 143&ndash;153).', 'michelle koo', 'Stephen G. Tilley (Chair), Richard Highton, David B. Wake', '', 0, 0, 0),
(516, 'desmognathus', 'brimleyorum', '', 'ouachita dusky salamander', '', '', '', 'caudata', 'salamanders', 'dusky salamanders', '', 'caudata', 'baird', 'stejneger', '{"1850": "1895"}', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0, 0),
(517, 'desmognathus', 'carolinensis', '', 'carolina mountain dusky salamander', '', '', '', 'caudata', 'salamanders', 'dusky salamanders', '', 'caudata', 'baird', 'dunn', '{&quot;1850&quot;:&quot;1916&quot;}', '', 'Tilley et al. (2013, Ecol. and Evol., 3: 2547&ndash;2567) reported on a molecularly distinctive form in the southern Bald Mountains and northern foothills of the Great Smoky Mountains that is phenotypically indistinguishable from this species. This form appears to hybridize with both *D. carolinensis* and *D. santeetlah* in the Blue Ridge Physiographic Province, and with an innominate lowland form further west in the Ridge and Valley Physiographic Province.', 'michelle koo', 'Stephen G. Tilley (Chair), Richard Highton, David B. Wake', '', 0, 0, 0),
(518, 'desmognathus', 'conanti', '', 'spotted dusky salamander', '', '', '', 'caudata', 'salamanders', 'dusky salamanders', '', 'caudata', 'baird', 'rossman', '{&quot;1850&quot;:&quot;1958&quot;}', '', 'Populations in the Ridge and Valley Physiographic Province.of eastern Tennessee appear to hybridize with this form but Tilley et al. (2013, Ecol. and Evol., 3: 2547&ndash;2567) declined to assign them to D. conanti due to their unique mitochondrial haplotypes. ', 'michelle koo', 'Stephen G. Tilley (Chair), Richard Highton, David B. Wake', '', 0, 0, 0),
(519, 'desmognathus', 'folkertsi', '', 'dwarf black-bellied salamander', '', '', '', 'caudata', 'salamanders', 'dusky salamanders', '', 'caudata', 'baird', 'camp, tilley, austin, and marshall', '{"1850": "2002"}', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0, 0),
(520, 'desmognathus', 'fuscus', '', 'northern dusky salamander', '', '', '', 'caudata', 'salamanders', 'dusky salamanders', '', 'caudata', 'baird', 'rafinesque', '{&quot;1850&quot;:&quot;1820&quot;}', '', 'Molecular data suggest deep differentiation among populations that morphologically resemble *D. fuscus* (Bonett, 2002, Copeia 2002: 344&ndash;355; Kozak, et al., 2005, Evolution 59: 2000&ndash;2016), and additional species almost certainly await resolution. ', 'michelle koo', 'Stephen G. Tilley (Chair), Richard Highton, David B. Wake', '', 0, 0, 0),
(521, 'desmognathus', 'imitator', '', 'imitator salamander', '', '', '', 'caudata', 'salamanders', 'dusky salamanders', '', 'caudata', 'baird', 'dunn', '{"1850": "1927"}', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0, 0),
(522, 'desmognathus', 'marmoratus', '', 'shovel-nosed salamander', '', '', '', 'caudata', 'salamanders', 'dusky salamanders', '', 'caudata', 'baird', 'moore', '{&quot;1850&quot;:&quot;1899&quot;}', '', 'Molecular data indicate that this taxon and *D. quadramaculatus* may not be reciprocally monophyletic (Rissler and Taylor, 2003, Mol. Phylogenet. Evol. 27: 197&ndash;211; Kozak, et al., 2005, Evolution 59: 2000&ndash;2016; Jones et al. 2006, Mol. Phylogenet. Evol. 38: 280&ndash;287; Wooten and Rissler, 2011, Acta Herpetol. 6: 175&ndash;208). None of these studies propose taxonomic revisions but Dubois and Rafa&euml;lli (2012, Alytes 28: 77&ndash;161) and Fouquette and Dubois (2014, A Checklist of North American Amphibians and Reptiles, The United States and Canada, Seventh Edition, Vol. 1 &ndash; Amphibians, Xlibris, San Bernardino, CA, 613 p.) resurrect two taxa, *D.aureatus* and *D. melanius*, from synonymy under this species (Martof , 1962, Am. Midl. Nat., 67: 30).', 'michelle koo', 'Stephen G. Tilley (Chair), Richard Highton, David B. Wake', '', 0, 0, 0),
(523, 'desmognathus', 'monticola', '', 'seal salamander', '', '', '', 'caudata', 'salamanders', 'dusky salamanders', '', 'caudata', 'baird', 'dunn', '{"1850": "1916"}', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0, 0),
(524, 'desmognathus', 'ochrophaeus', '', ' allegheny mountains dusky salamander', '', '', '', 'caudata', 'salamanders', 'dusky salamanders', '', 'caudata', 'baird', 'cope', '{"1850": "1859"}', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0, 0),
(525, 'desmognathus', 'ocoee', '', 'ocoee salamander', '', '', '', 'caudata', 'salamanders', 'dusky salamanders', '', 'caudata', 'baird', 'nicholls', '{&quot;1850&quot;:&quot;1949&quot;}', '', 'This form consists of numerous parapatric units that occupy different mountain ranges in the southern Blue Ridge and Cumberland Plateau physiographic provinces and probably represent distinct species (Tilley and Mahoney, 1996, Herpetol. Monogr. 10: 1&ndash;42; Tilley, 1997, J. Heredity 88: 305&ndash;315; Highton, 2000, in R. C. Bruce, B. G. Jaeger and L. D, Houck [eds.], The Biology of Plethodontid Salamanders. Kluwer Academic/Plenum Publishers, New York, Pp. 215&ndash;241).  ', 'michelle koo', 'Stephen G. Tilley (Chair), Richard Highton, David B. Wake', '', 0, 0, 0),
(526, 'desmognathus', 'orestes', '', 'blue ridge dusky salamander', '', '', '', 'caudata', 'salamanders', 'dusky salamanders', '', 'caudata', 'baird', 'tilley and manhoney', '{&quot;1850&quot;:&quot;1996&quot;}', '', 'This taxon consists of two genetically differentiated units that may represent cryptic species (Tilley and Mahoney, 1996, Herpetol. Monogr. 10: 1&ndash;42; Tilley, 1997, J. Heredity 88: 305&ndash;315; Highton, 2000, in R. C. Bruce, B. G. Jaeger and L. D, Houck [eds.], The Biology of Plethodontid Salamanders. Kluwer Academic/Plenum Publishers, New York, pp. 215&ndash;241).', 'michelle koo', 'Stephen G. Tilley (Chair), Richard Highton, David B. Wake', '', 0, 0, 0),
(527, 'desmognathus', 'organi', '', 'northern pygmy salamander', '', '', '', 'caudata', 'salamanders', 'dusky salamanders', '', 'caudata', 'baird', 'crespi, brown, and rissler', '{"1850": "2010"}', '', '', NULL, NULL, '', 0, 0, 0),
