(662, 'pseudotriton', 'montanus', '', 'mud salamander', '', '', '', 'caudata', 'salamanders', 'red and mud salamanders', '', 'caudata', 'tschudi', 'baird', '{&quot;1838&quot;:&quot;1850&quot;}', '', 'Fouquette and Dubois (2014, A Checklist of North American Amphibians and Reptiles, The United States and Canada, Seventh Edition, Vol. 1 &ndash; Amphibians, Xlibris, San Bernardino, CA, 613 p.) transfer this species to the genus *Gyrinophilus*, citing the cladogram published by Bonnet, et al. (Bonett, et al. (2013 [2014], Evolution 68: 466&ndash;482). Those authors, however, refrained from recommending this treatment on the basis of their phylogeny and relationships among forms of *Pseudotriton* and *Gyrinophilus* lack strong statistical support in their analysis.  ', 'michelle koo', 'Stephen G. Tilley (Chair), Richard Highton, David B. Wake', '', 0, 0, 0),
(663, 'pseudotriton', 'montanus', 'diastictus', 'midland mud salamander', '', '', '', 'caudata', 'salamanders', 'red and mud salamanders', '', 'caudata', 'tschudi', 'bishop', '{&quot;1839&quot;:&quot;1941&quot;}', '', 'This taxon was elevated to a full species by Collins (1991, Herpet. Rev. 22: 42&ndash;43).  This treatment has been followed by Dubois and Raffa&euml;lli (2012, Alytes 28: 77&ndash;161) and Raffa&euml;lli (2013, Les Urod&egrave;les du Monde, 2e  edition, Penclen &Eacute;dition, France &ndash; no city given).  Fouquette and Dubois (2014, A Checklist of North American Amphibians and Reptiles, The United States and Canada, Seventh Edition, Vol. 1 &ndash; Amphibians, Xlibris, San Bernardino, CA, 613 p.) also treat it as a subspecies of *P. montanus*, which they transfer to *Gyrinophilus*. The phylogeny presented by Bonett, et al. (2013 [2014], Evolution 68: 466&ndash;482) indicates a sister relationship between this taxon and *P. montanus*. In the absence of data on levels of genetic differentiation, we retain the original taxonomic status of this form (Bishop, 1941, Occ. Pap. Mus. Zool. Univ. Mich., 451: 1&ndash;27).', 'michelle koo', 'Stephen G. Tilley (Chair), Richard Highton, David B. Wake', '', 0, 0, 0),
