(676, 'siren', 'intermedia', '', 'lesser siren', '', '', '', 'caudata', 'salamanders', 'sirens', '', 'caudata', 'osterdam', 'barnes', '{&quot;1766&quot;:&quot;1826&quot;}', '', '*S. i. texana* was synonymized with *S. intermedia nettingi* by Flores-Villela and Brandon (1992, Ann. Carnegie Mus. 61: 289&ndash;291) but Dubois and Raffa&euml;lli (2012, Alytes 28: 77&ndash;161) and Fouquette and Dubois (2014, A Checklist of North American Amphibians and Reptiles, The United States and Canada, Seventh Edition, Vol. 1 &ndash; Amphibians, Xlibris, San Bernardino, CA, 613 p.) considered that subspecies to be valid. The taxonomic statuses of this and the remaining subspecies remain unclear and deserve careful evaluation. ', 'michelle koo', 'Stephen G. Tilley (Chair), Richard Highton, David B. Wake', '', 0, 0, 0),
