(1026, 'urosaurus', 'ornatus', '', 'ornate tree lizard', '', '', '', 'squamata', '', 'tree and brush lizards', '', 'squamata', 'hallowell', 'baird and girard', '{&quot;1854&quot;:&quot;1852&quot;}', '', 'Taxonomy for Urosaurus follows (Mittleman, 1942, Bull. Mus. Comp. Zool. 91: 103&ndash;181). Haenel (2007, Mol. Ecol. 16: 4321&ndash;4334) found substantial phylogeographic structure in the mtDNA of *U. ornatus*, some of which is roughly consistent with previously recognized subspecies (e.g., *U. o. wrighti* from the Colorado Plateau), though other aspects are not (e.g., deep splits within *U. o. schottii*, including some inferred clades for which there are available names).  The phylogeography of *U. ornatus* deserves further study, particularly with regard to taxonomic implications.', 'kelsey lyberger', 'Kevin de Quieroz (Chair) and Tod W. Reeder', '', 0, 0, 0),
(1028, 'necturus', 'lodingi', '', 'mobile waterdog', '', '', '', 'caudata', '', 'waterdogs and mudpuppies', '', 'caudata', 'rafinesque', 'viosca', '{"1819":"1937"}', '', 'Raffalli (2013, Les Urodles du Monde, 2e  edition, Penclen dition, France  no city given) and Fouquette and Dubois (2014, A Checklist of North American Amphibians and Reptiles, The United States and Canada, Seventh Edition, Vol. 1  Amphibians, Xlibris, San Bernardino, CA, 613 p.) recognize *N. lodingi* as a full species.', 'michelle koo', 'Stephen G. Tilley (Chair), Richard Highton, David B. Wake', '', 0, 0, 0),
(1029, 'necturus', 'louisianensis', '', 'red river waterdog', '', '', '', 'caudata', '', 'waterdogs and mudpuppies', '', 'caudata', 'rafinesque', 'viosca', '{"1819":"1938"}', '', 'Collins (1991, Herpet. Rev. 22: 4243), Raffalli (2013, Les Urodles du Monde, 2e  edition, Penclen dition, France  no city given) and Fouquette and Dubois (2014, A Checklist of North American Amphibians and Reptiles, The United States and Canada, Seventh Edition, Vol. 1  Amphibians, Xlibris, San Bernardino, CA, 613 p.) recognize *N. louisianensis* as a full species.', 'michelle koo', 'Stephen G. Tilley (Chair), Richard Highton, David B. Wake', '', 0, 0, 0),
(1033, 'utahraptor', 'ostrommaysorum', '', 'utahraptor (test)', 'species&#95;photos/utahraptor&#95;updated.png', 'emily willoughby (e.deinonychus@gmail.com, http://emilywilloughby.com)', 'cc by-sa 3.0', 'dinosauria', 'raptor', 'theropoda', 'dromaeosauridae', 'dinosauria', 'kirkland', 'kirkland', '{&quot;1993&quot;:&quot;1993 \\&quot;2015\\&quot;&quot;}', '{&quot;Deprecated species&quot;:&quot;Person: 2015&quot;,&quot;Second Species&quot;:&quot;Person: 2012&quot;}', 'but as a species by Wright (1993, in J. W. Wright and L. J. Vitt [eds.], Biology of Whiptail Lizards [Genus Cnemidophorus], Oklahoma Mus. Nat. Hist., Pp. 27&ndash;81). Rissler and Apodaca (2007, Syst. Biol. 56: 924&ndash;942) conclude, on the basis of mitochondrial DNA phylogeography and ecological niche modeling, that this taxon should be subdivided into two or more species. Dubois and Raffa&euml;lli (2012, Alytes 28: 77&ndash;161) formally recognize A. iecanus Cope, 1883, niger Myers and Maslin, 1948, and a nomen nudum, &ldquo;sequoiensis&rdquo; Lowe, 1950, the latter based on an unpublished thesis. Reilly et al. (2013, Diversity 5: 657&ndash;679) used nuclear and mitochondrial DNA to show that northern populations in the Klamath, Smith and Rogue River drainages are genetically distinct from other populations but made no taxonomic changes. Raffa&euml;lli (2013, Les Urod&egrave;les du Monde, 2e edition, Penclen &Eacute;dition, France &ndash; no city given) recognizes A. niger and A. i&euml;canus (although diacritical marks are not to be used in scientific names), and also refers to an unnamed subspecies of A. flavipunctatus that he formerly treated as &ldquo;sequoiensis&rdquo; by the French vernacular name &ldquo;An&eacute;ides noir de l&rsquo;Est&rdquo;. Furthermore, he refers to the populations identified by Reilly et al. (2012, Molec. Ecol. 2012: 5745&ndash;5761) as an unnamed species, to which he applies the French vernacular name &ldquo;An&eacute;ides noir du Nord&rdquo;. Fouquette and Dubois (2014, A Checklist of North American Amphibians and Reptiles, The United States and Canada, Seventh Edition, Vol. 1 &ndash; Amphibians, Xlibris, San Bernardino, CA, 613 p.) do not recognize the subspecies listed below. Studies in progress will clarify the taxonomy of this complex.', 'philip kahn', 'Wikipedia', 'foobar', 1, 0, 0),
